subSubSection.paragraph:
Scales ctenoid with peripheral cteni (
Roberts 1993
), those on top of head smaller and reaching forward to just in front of nostrils; no accessory scales on head or body; first infraorbital naked; maxilla scaly; small scales basally on segmented ray bases of dorsal and anal fins; small scales basally extending about three fourths of distance to margin of caudal fin; pelvic fins without axillary scales, but with patch of variable-sized scales between bases of fins; lateral line continuous, arched over pectoral fin, forming angle as it joins straight peduncular portion.
